From f7791aafbf6aded9b2cc9c81eacb6cce796a58d8 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: ci <ci@local>
Date: Thu, 11 Jun 2026 06:27:35 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] dpaa: add CEETM HTB-offload egress shaper consumer

Add a TC_SETUP_QDISC_HTB offload consumer that bridges the stock iproute2
HTB-offload contract ("tc qdisc add dev ethX root handle 1: htb offload")
to the QMan CEETM hierarchical egress traffic manager core added in the
preceding commit. This replaces the legacy custom "ceetm" qdisc with the
modern mlx5/nfp-style HTB offload pattern.

New files dpaa_ceetm.{c,h} implement a flat root->leaf mapping:

  - TC_HTB_CREATE claims a CEETM sub-portal + LNI, maps SP->LNI (enabling
    CEETM mode on the FMan Tx port) and builds an unshaped default channel.
  - each HTB leaf class -> its own CEETM channel on the shared LNI, with
    the channel dual-rate shaper set to commit-rate = class rate and
    excess-rate = class ceil, plus a single strict-priority class queue
    and a byte-mode tail-drop CCG. The leaf is exposed as Tx queue
    base + slot (base = dpaa_max_num_txqs()).
  - TC_HTB_NODE_MODIFY reprograms the channel rates; TC_HTB_LEAF_DEL tears
    a leaf down; TC_HTB_LEAF_QUERY_QUEUE maps classid -> Tx queue.
  - TC_HTB_LEAF_TO_INNER and deeper hierarchies are rejected -EOPNOTSUPP.

Because sp_set_lni() stops the conventional WQ egress FQs, dpaa_xmit()
steers ALL egress (including the XDP Tx path) through the CEETM hierarchy
while priv->ceetm is published: leaf Tx queues hit their own LFQ, every
other queue falls back to the default channel. The netdev is allocated
with DPAA_CEETM_MAX_TXQS (32) extra Tx queues and real_num_tx_queues is
grown/restored as leaves come and go. CCG tail-drop rejections arrive as
software ERNs and are counted as Tx drops.

The dpaa_eth.c hooks are gated on CONFIG_DPAA_HW_CEETM with header stubs
for the disabled build. count_ern()/dpaa_cleanup_tx_fd() are de-static'd
and the enum port_type is promoted to dpaa_eth.h so the new file can share
them. The 0104b CEETM scaffold (dpaa_ceetm_qdisc_install/destroy/supported
and struct dpaa_ceetm_config) is removed from dpaa_fman_caps.{c,h} and the
Kconfig entry is rewritten to depend on FSL_QMAN_CEETM.

Co-authored-by: Copilot <223556219+Copilot@users.noreply.github.com>
